(4, 'Megawide builds Phirst Park Homes in General Trias', '<div class=\"ewa-rteLine\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Calibri, Thonburi, Arial, Verdana, sans-serif, &quot;Mongolian Baiti&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yi Baiti&quot;, &quot;Javanese Text&quot;; font-size: 1px; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri; font-size: 14pt;\">Megawide is undertaking its eighth project with PHirst Park Homes, Inc. (PPHI) in General Trias, Cavite. It will supply and build 1,664 housing units using its top-notch precast materials. </span></div><div class=\"ewa-rteLine\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); white-space: pre-wrap; font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11pt;\"><br></div><div class=\"ewa-rteLine\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Calibri, Thonburi, Arial, Verdana, sans-serif, &quot;Mongolian Baiti&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yi Baiti&quot;, &quot;Javanese Text&quot;; font-size: 1px; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri; font-size: 14pt;\">The housing project will benefit from Megawide’s proprietary precast technology that enables speed to market with its quick turnaround time. The product’s consistency also reduces long-term costs by limiting manpower needs and minimizing rework.</span></div>', '', '2022-09-26 21:41:47', '2022-09-27 18:31:37', '2022-09-27 18:31:37'),
(14, 'Megawide donates new fire station to Taytay', '<div class=\"ewa-rteLine\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Calibri, Thonburi, Arial, Verdana, sans-serif, &quot;Mongolian Baiti&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yi Baiti&quot;, &quot;Javanese Text&quot;; font-size: 1px; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri; font-size: 14pt;\">Megawide and Bureau of Fire Protection (BFP) broke ground last July 27 for a brand-new fire station in Taytay, a donation of the company to the community. The 1.2 million-worth of facility is expected to boost the municipality’s emergency response in cases of fire and other emergencies. Megawide will undertake the site, structural, and civil works, including mechanical, electrical, plumbing and fire protection (MEPF) services.  </span></div><div class=\"ewa-rteLine\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); white-space: pre-wrap; font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11pt;\"><br></div><div class=\"ewa-rteLine\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Calibri, Thonburi, Arial, Verdana, sans-serif, &quot;Mongolian Baiti&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yi Baiti&quot;, &quot;Javanese Text&quot;; font-size: 1px; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri; font-size: 14pt;\">The groundbreaking ceremony, which signals the start of construction, was led by the officials of BFP Taytay and Megawide.</span><strong style=\"font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"> </span></strong></div>', '', '2022-09-26 21:44:04', '2022-10-12 08:46:08', '2022-10-12 08:46:08'),
(24, 'Cebu City\'s Newest Landmark', '<div class=\"ewa-rteLine\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Calibri, Thonburi, Arial, Verdana, sans-serif, &quot;Mongolian Baiti&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yi Baiti&quot;, &quot;Javanese Text&quot;; font-size: 1px; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri; font-size: 14pt;\">A new landmark statue that signifies Cebu’s path towards a modernized market stood at the Sto. Nino Chapel within the Carbon Market premises. The 30-feet Sto. Nino statue is part of the  P5.5billion Carbon Market Redevelopment Project in Cebu City. </span></div><div class=\"ewa-rteLine\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); white-space: pre-wrap; font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11pt;\"><br></div><div class=\"ewa-rteLine\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Calibri, Thonburi, Arial, Verdana, sans-serif, &quot;Mongolian Baiti&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yi Baiti&quot;, &quot;Javanese Text&quot;; font-size: 1px; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri; font-size: 14pt;\">Cebuanos can pray and hold special celebrations at the new chapel after a Memorandum of Agreement (MOA) between Cebu2World with the Archdiocese of Cebu and the City Government allowed the resumption of religious activities. Aside from that, the Interim Market Building and the Bagsakan Center also started operating to provide a better environment for selling for Carbon vendors.</span></div>', '', '2022-09-26 21:46:04', '2022-10-12 08:46:12', '2022-10-12 08:46:12'),
(34, 'Megawide’s Plumera project recognized for concrete construction excellence', '<div class=\"ewa-rteLine\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Calibri, Thonburi, Arial, Verdana, sans-serif, &quot;Mongolian Baiti&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yi Baiti&quot;, &quot;Javanese Text&quot;; font-size: 1px; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri; font-size: 14pt;\">Megawide bagged the Mid-Rise Category for excellence in this year’s Philippine Excellence in Concrete Construction Awards (PECCA) for its construction of the Plumera Mactan project in Lapu-Lapu City, Cebu — a development by Cebuano company Johndorf Ventures. Megawide is undertaking design and construction works for the project.</span></div><div class=\"ewa-rteLine\" bold-block=\"true\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); white-space: pre-wrap; font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11pt;\"><br></div><div class=\"ewa-rteLine\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Calibri, Thonburi, Arial, Verdana, sans-serif, &quot;Mongolian Baiti&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yi Baiti&quot;, &quot;Javanese Text&quot;; font-size: 1px; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri; font-size: 14pt;\">The award recognizes projects with outstanding use of innovation and technology, and for inspiring excellence throughout the global construction community</span></div>', '', '2022-09-26 21:54:59', '2022-10-12 08:46:16', '2022-10-12 08:46:16'),
(44, 'test', 'test', '', '2022-09-27 17:16:07', '2022-09-27 17:16:16', '2022-09-27 17:16:16'),
(54, 'Megawide, DOtr sign contract package 104 for Metro Manila Subway Project', '<div class=\"ewa-rteLine\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Calibri, Thonburi, Arial, Verdana, sans-serif, &quot;Mongolian Baiti&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yi Baiti&quot;, &quot;Javanese Text&quot;; font-size: 1px; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri; font-size: 14pt;\">Our first underground train line is shaping up! Megawide Construction Corp., together with its Japanese partners, Tokyu Construction and Tobishima Corporation, officially signed the P17.75-billion Metro Manila Subway Project Contract Package 104 (CP-104) of the Department of Transporation (DOTr) last May 5. </span></div><div class=\"ewa-rteLine\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); white-space: pre-wrap; font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11pt;\"><br></div><div class=\"ewa-rteLine\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Calibri, Thonburi, Arial, Verdana, sans-serif, &quot;Mongolian Baiti&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yi Baiti&quot;, &quot;Javanese Text&quot;; font-size: 1px; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri; font-size: 14pt;\">Described as a “game changer” by Megawide Chairman and CEO Edgar Saavedra, the package covers the construction of the underground stations in Ortigas Station and Shaw Station as well as the tunnels connecting these two locations.</span><strong style=\"font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">  </span></strong></div>', '', '2022-09-27 17:32:35', '2022-10-12 08:46:22', '2022-10-12 08:46:22'),
(64, 'Megawide, PH1 break ground for Ortigas Hills Project', '<div class=\"ewa-rteLine\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Calibri, Thonburi, Arial, Verdana, sans-serif, &quot;Mongolian Baiti&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yi Baiti&quot;, &quot;Javanese Text&quot;; font-size: 1px; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri; font-size: 14pt;\">Extraordinary developer PH1 World Developers and Megawide Construction Corp. have started the construction of the Ortigas Hills Project in Taytay, Rizal following a groundbreaking ceremony held in August.</span></div><div class=\"ewa-rteLine\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Calibri, Thonburi, Arial, Verdana, sans-serif, &quot;Mongolian Baiti&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yi Baiti&quot;, &quot;Javanese Text&quot;; font-size: 1px; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri; font-size: 14pt;\"> </span></div><div class=\"ewa-rteLine\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Calibri, Thonburi, Arial, Verdana, sans-serif, &quot;Mongolian Baiti&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yi Baiti&quot;, &quot;Javanese Text&quot;; font-size: 1px; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri; font-size: 14pt;\">The project, Megawide’s third venture in the municipality, consists of three mid-rise condominium buildings in a 16,470 sq m. property in Ortigas Extension, Brgy. San Isidro, Taytay, Rizal. The Ortigas Hills Project will boast PH1’s promise of Extra Space at No Extra Cost, through its exclusive AddLoft Technology</span></div>', '', '2022-09-27 18:03:15', '2022-10-12 08:46:28', '2022-10-12 08:46:28'),
