(154, 'Megawide donates new fire station to Taytay', '<div class=\"ewa-rteLine\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Calibri, Thonburi, Arial, Verdana, sans-serif, &quot;Mongolian Baiti&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yi Baiti&quot;, &quot;Javanese Text&quot;; font-size: 1px; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 18pt;\">Megawide and Bureau of Fire Protection (BFP) broke ground last July 27 for a brand-new fire station in Taytay, a donation of the company to the community. The 1.2 million-worth of facility is expected to boost the municipality’s emergency response in cases of fire and other emergencies. Megawide will undertake the site, structural, and civil works, including mechanical, electrical, plumbing and fire protection (MEPF) services. </span></div><div class=\"ewa-rteLine\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); white-space: pre-wrap; font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11pt;\"><br></div><div class=\"ewa-rteLine\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Calibri, Thonburi, Arial, Verdana, sans-serif, &quot;Mongolian Baiti&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yi Baiti&quot;, &quot;Javanese Text&quot;; font-size: 1px; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 18pt;\">The groundbreaking ceremony, which signals the start of construction, was led by the officials of BFP Taytay and Megawide.</span></div>', '', '2022-10-18 06:08:52', '2022-10-18 06:08:52', NULL),
