(164, 'Workplace safety is Megawide’s priority', '<div class=\"OutlineElement Ltr SCXW164366494 BCX8\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; user-select: text; -webkit-user-drag: none; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; overflow: visible; cursor: text; clear: both; position: relative; direction: ltr;\"><div class=\"OutlineElement Ltr SCXW164366494 BCX8\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; user-select: text; -webkit-user-drag: none; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; overflow: visible; cursor: text; clear: both; position: relative; direction: ltr;\"><p class=\"Paragraph SCXW164366494 BCX8\" xml:lang=\"EN-US\" lang=\"EN-US\" paraid=\"760333815\" paraeid=\"{6fde7e5b-c422-4d90-a826-72e1afd8dd7c}{156}\" style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; user-select: text; -webkit-user-drag: none; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; overflow-wrap: break-word; vertical-align: baseline; font-kerning: none; background-color: transparent; text-align: justify;\"><font color=\"#000000\" face=\"Helvetica\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px; font-variant-ligatures: none; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Megawide values the welfare of its employees and part of this is ensuring they are equipped with the right knowledge on workplace safety and health.  \r\n \r\nMegawide Corporate employees recently underwent training on Occupational Safety and Health led by Health, Safety, Security and Environment (HSSE) Senior Manager Christopher Tamayo and Precast and Construction Solutions (PCS) Safety Advisor Ramil Diaz. The discussion involved the prohibited acts and penalties in Occupational Safety and Health, office safety hazards and office ergonomics where employees shared their insights too.  \r\n\r\nThe eight-hour Occupational Safety and Health training is mandated by the Department of Labor and Employment (DOLE) to certify that the company’s practices and environment support employees’ safety at work.  \r\n\r\nMegawide has been implementing effective programs in Occupational Safety and Health. In fact, this was recognized by DOLE as the company has tallied a total of 24 million safe-man hours across its construction sites last year:  \r\n\r\nMay 2022:<b> </b>PH1’s The Hive project site – 2 million \r\nJuly 2022: Suntrust’s Westside City Site B, Paranaque – 5 million; and Megawide Industrial Plant, Taytay – 13 million \r\nSeptember 2022: Megaworld’s Gentry Manor – 3 million; and Prince Jun’s University Tower 5 – 1 million </span></font><br></p></div></div><p>								              		\r\n								              	</p>', NULL, '2023-03-13 03:40:43', '2023-03-13 08:44:33', NULL);
