(171, 'In tree planting, Megawide commits to protecting the environment', '<div class=\"OutlineElement Ltr SCXW124859552 BCX8\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; user-select: text; -webkit-user-drag: none; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; overflow: visible; cursor: text; clear: both; position: relative; direction: ltr;\"><div class=\"OutlineElement Ltr SCXW124859552 BCX8\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; user-select: text; -webkit-user-drag: none; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; overflow: visible; cursor: text; clear: both; position: relative; direction: ltr;\"><p class=\"Paragraph SCXW124859552 BCX8\" xml:lang=\"EN-US\" lang=\"EN-US\" paraid=\"288207361\" paraeid=\"{c6cc28a3-a046-4f85-8e27-eb06eda264df}{211}\" style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; user-select: text; -webkit-user-drag: none; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; overflow-wrap: break-word; vertical-align: baseline; font-kerning: none; background-color: transparent; text-align: justify;\"><font color=\"#000000\" face=\"Helvetica\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px; font-variant-ligatures: none; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Protecting the environment is a shared responsibility, one which requires the world\'s builders to take part. Some shun the task; those who accept reveal their character. \r\n\r\nIn October 2022, Megawide made its commitment to the planet’s health unmistakable, planting tree seedlings as part of its Westside City project. Megawide intends for the trees to \"grow big and benefit the communities, now and in the future.\" \r\n\r\nMegawide planted 50 seedlings at the La Mesa Watershed Nursery Seedling, a venue recommended by the Department of Environment and Natural Resources (DENR) in Bicutan, Taguig.  \r\n\r\nThe company intends for the trees to \"grow big and benefit the communities, now and in the future” taking an effort to implement projects best aligned with practices in environmental conservation.  \r\n\r\nMegawide has long been intent on advancing their environmental efforts. Various initiatives, in fact, were realized in 2022:  \r\n\r\nAglipay Sewage Treatment Plant (STP) Tree Planting  \r\n\r\nThe activity was held at La Mesa Eco Park in August 2022, and acquired the help of 15 volunteers. Project Manager Eleazar Sanchez and CSR project champion Ara Amores led the group. 400 native trees were planted during the event.  \r\n\r\nEPC Tree Planting  \r\n\r\nEPC employees had been encouraged to use a bamboo toothbrush, which were then planted as tree seedlings during the September 6 and 13 dates at Caranglan, Nueva Ecija. \r\n\r\nCiticore CommuniTree Project  \r\n\r\nCiticore Power Inc. led the Communitree Project through Citicore Foundation, which counts \"stewardship for environment\" among its core values. The project was a tree-planting initiative in partnership with the Department of Environment and Natural Resources - Community Environment and Natural Resources Office (DENR-CENRO) in Baliuag, Bulacan. In October 2022, Citicore and Megawide Foundation employees planted 300 Guyabano at Sierra Madre Mountain Range in Barangay Kalawakan, Dona Remedios Trinidad, Bulacan. </span></font><br></p></div></div>', NULL, '2023-03-13 10:43:32', '2023-03-13 10:43:32', NULL),
