(190, 'MeGabay: An ordinary tour turned extraordinary', '<div style=\"text-align: justify; \"><div><font face=\"Helvetica\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">On the second MeGabay session of Megawide Foundation, engineering and architecture student scholars from Pamantasan ng Lungsod ng Maynila, Polytechnic University of the Philippines and Technological University of the Philippines toured around the projects of extraordinary property developer and Megawide’s sister company, PH1 World Developers, last April 25.&nbsp;</span></font></div><div><font face=\"Helvetica\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">&nbsp;</span></font></div><div><font face=\"Helvetica\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">The tour began at PH1’s flagship project The Hive Residences in Taytay, Rizal, learning the basics of engineering works in building the project with Project Development Manager Erika Angeles and Project Manager John Caday. The scholars also visited Modan Lofts Ortigas Hills where they were brought down the 28 ft. deep excavated ground with Safety Officers, then finally capped off the tour at MyEnso Lofts in Timog Avenue, Quezon City. Jewel Deocaris, an Architecture student of PLM, shared how amazed she was with PH1’s projects, more so, how insightful the tour was.</span></font></div><div><font face=\"Helvetica\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><br></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Helvetica\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">“Hindi lang pala basta basta ‘yong mga ganitong klase ng projects. Innovative ‘yong mga works and processes at lahat sinisigurado which I believe is very important especially for residential projects,” she shared.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></font></div><div><font face=\"Helvetica\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><br></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Helvetica\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">\"Through this site tour, scholars are exposed to invaluable learnings that go beyond textbooks as they are immersed in First-World engineering projects and developments which are important to them. The legacy of excellence and innovation is passed on, creating a ripple effect that shapes the landscape of engineering a First-world Philippines,” shared CSR champion for Megawide Corporate Timothy Osma.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></font></div></div><span style=\"font-size: 18px; font-family: Helvetica;\">								              		\r\n								              	</span>', NULL, '2023-05-12 02:35:53', '2023-05-12 02:41:27', NULL),
(191, 'Megawide leader: A good problem-solver, a firm decision-maker', '<div style=\"text-align: justify; \"><div><font face=\"Helvetica\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Corporate Human Resources Learning and Talent Management (LTM) team launched the second installment in the Lead to Drive Business Results series, providing an insightful leadership training for the officers and managers of Megawide Corporate, last April 3 and 4.&nbsp;</span></font></div><div><br></div><div><font face=\"Helvetica\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Educator and management consultant Jamesina Gotangco facilitated the two-day training on critical thinking, problem analysis, decision analysis, creative and systems thinking, and integrating all of them.&nbsp;</span></font></div><div><br></div><div><font face=\"Helvetica\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">This training is still part of LTM’s initiative of developing the skills of employees by ensuring that they complete 25 hours minimum of both technical and leadership trainings this year, which can come from department-initiated trainings focused on performance-based competencies and Megawide University online training programs.</span></font></div><div><font face=\"Helvetica\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><br></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Helvetica\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Donelle Umali, Public Policy Supervisor of CCAB, shared how the problem analysis and decision-making frameworks would be of great help in her work in Issues and Crisis Management.&nbsp;</span></font></div><div><br></div><div><font face=\"Helvetica\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">“The new approaches introduced forces me to think more critically and creatively whenever I encounter issues at work. Instead of making decisions based on information at face value, I\'m encouraged to keep asking \"Why?\" until I get to the underlying cause. This way, I can come up with possible alternative solutions to address problems effectively,\" she shared.&nbsp;</span></font></div><div><br></div><div><font face=\"Helvetica\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Continue to upskill by engaging with more training at the Megawide University! Click this link: https://university.megawide.com.ph/.&nbsp;</span></font></div></div><span style=\"font-size: 18px; font-family: Helvetica;\">								              		\r\n								              	</span>', NULL, '2023-05-12 02:49:57', '2023-05-12 02:49:57', NULL),
(192, 'Spotlight: A new feat for our very own Boss Ed', '<div><span style=\"font-size: 18px; font-family: Helvetica;\">\"True Lasallian\" has long been a descriptor for Megawide Chairman and CEO Edgar Saavedra. In April, the university simply made common knowledge official, recognizing the infrastructure giant for building a storied career outside of its halls.&nbsp;</span></div><div><br></div><div><span style=\"font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 18px;\">On April 16, the De La Salle Alumni Association (DLSAA) conferred Saavedra the DLSAA Lasallian Achievement Award in Civil Engineering and Infrastructure Development. The award was based on his \"outstanding leadership of the nation\'s top and trailblazing companies that set landmark industry standards in the fields of construction, infrastructure, and engineering.\"&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></div><div><br></div><div><span style=\"font-size: 18px; font-family: Helvetica;\">Boss Ed studied Civil Engineering at the university, earning his degree in 1995.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></div><div><br></div><div><span style=\"font-size: 18px; font-family: Helvetica;\">In his short acceptance speech, Boss Ed thanked the DLSAA, and underscored the Lasallian values that helped propel his career. Saavedra stressed that a \"true Lasallian\" embraces a culture of humility and being sociable, which he said proved more important to his success than being smartest.&nbsp;</span></div>', NULL, '2023-05-12 02:53:14', '2023-05-12 02:53:14', NULL),
(193, 'Megawide captures 4th PECCA award', '<div style=\"text-align: justify; \"><div><font face=\"Helvetica\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">A big win for concrete engineering excellence!</span></font></div><div><font face=\"Helvetica\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><br></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Helvetica\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Megawide’s Sto. Nino Chapel bagged the Decorative Concrete Award at the Philippine Excellence in Concrete Construction Awards (PECCA) last March 30.&nbsp;</span></font></div><div><font face=\"Helvetica\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><br></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Helvetica\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">The chapel is part of the Carbon District Modernization project between Megawide subsidiary C2W, and the city government of Cebu.</span></font></div><div><font face=\"Helvetica\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><br></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Helvetica\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">The chapel was built with reinforced concrete and the wave-like roof design was inspired by Cebu’s Sinulog dance. The use of reinforced concrete special molds and formworks helped the successful application of this material.&nbsp;</span></font></div><div><font face=\"Helvetica\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><br></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Helvetica\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">The project was a joint effort between three Megawide units: C2W, Construction, and PCS-Formworks.&nbsp;</span></font></div><div><font face=\"Helvetica\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><br></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Helvetica\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">“We are honored to be recognized by PECCA for the fourth time. PECCA shows that the Philippine construction industry is committed to the development and application of world-class standards in the use of concrete in construction,” said Frederick Tan, Chief Operating Officer of Megawide’s Construction.&nbsp;</span></font></div><div><font face=\"Helvetica\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><br></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Helvetica\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">\"It is an honor for Cebu2World to bring Cebu\'s deeply rooted heritage to life through the Carbon Modernization project and showcase design and architecture that is reflective of our culture,\" said Lydwena Eco, Deputy General Manager of Cebu2World.</span></font></div><div><font face=\"Helvetica\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><br></span></font></div><div><font face=\"Helvetica\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">This is Megawide’s fourth recognition from PECCA: Mactan-Cebu International Airport won theBest Infrastructure Category while Paranaque Integrated Terminal Exchange (PITX) won Best Decorative Design both in 2021; Plumera Mactan won the Mid-Rise Structures Category in 2022.&nbsp;</span></font></div><div><br></div></div>', NULL, '2023-05-12 06:05:38', '2023-05-12 06:05:38', NULL),
(195, 'Morning with the Bossings is back!', '<div><span style=\"font-size: 18px; font-family: Helvetica;\">The latest developments and milestones of the whole Megawide group are brought to you by the “Morning with the Bossings!”&nbsp;</span></div><div><span style=\"font-size: 1rem;\"><br></span></div><div><span style=\"font-size: 18px; font-family: Helvetica;\">Watch the event here!&nbsp;</span><br></div><div><br></div><div><a href=\"https://megawideph.sharepoint.com/:v:/r/sites/HoldCoBranding-Branding/Shared%20Documents/005%20Branding.%20Events/001%20HLD%20Events/003%20MWTB/003%20MWTB%202023/HLD.BRD.%20MWTB%20May%2031%202023.mp4?csf=1&amp;web=1&amp;e=7O5zvQ\" target=\"_blank\">Morning with the Bossings </a></div>', NULL, '2023-06-29 11:04:36', '2023-06-29 11:04:36', NULL),
(196, 'PITX levels up, adds new routes and stores', '<div><div><span style=\"font-size: 18px; font-family: Helvetica;\">New routes and stores have enhanced the Paranaque Integrated Terminal Exchange (PITX) experience.&nbsp;</span></div><div><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><br></span></div><div><span style=\"font-size: 18px; font-family: Helvetica;\">MWM Terminals, the Megawide subsidiary operating the country’s first landport, has improved the terminal, adding seven new stores, nine new routes, and new facilities.&nbsp;</span></div><div><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><br></span></div><div><span style=\"font-size: 18px; font-family: Helvetica;\">The new routes for Luzon are North EDSA, Balagtas, Lancaster New City, Aseana Loop Service, Paracale, and Magallanes. Naval and Oras are new routes for Visayas; and a San Jose trip has been added for Mindanao.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></div><div><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><br></span></div><div><span style=\"font-size: 18px; font-family: Helvetica;\">PITX also features the following new chains: Tim Hortons, Food Terminal, The Hub, Cebuana Lhuiller, Waka Pares, Potato Giant, and Banh Mi.&nbsp;</span></div><div><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><br></span></div><div><span style=\"font-size: 18px; font-family: Helvetica;\">Keep posted with more PITX updates by visiting their website at www.pitx.com.ph.&nbsp; &nbsp;</span></div></div>', NULL, '2023-06-29 11:04:36', '2023-06-29 11:04:36', NULL),
(197, 'Megawide completes Plumera Mactan project', '<div><span style=\"font-size: 18px; font-family: Helvetica;\">Megawide finished construction of the Plumera Mactan project in Cebu last May.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></div><div><span style=\"font-size: 18px; font-family: Helvetica;\">&nbsp;</span></div><div><span style=\"font-size: 18px; font-family: Helvetica;\">The Plumera Mactan project is a development by Cebuano company Johndorf Ventures. Megawide fulfilled the contractor design and construction duties.&nbsp;</span></div><div><span style=\"font-size: 18px; font-family: Helvetica;\">&nbsp;</span></div><div><span style=\"font-size: 18px; font-family: Helvetica;\">Plumera is a 20-building condominium development located in Barangay Basak, Lapu-Lapu City, Cebu.&nbsp; Megawide used precast concrete as the main structural material for the project, enabling faster construction and minimizing costs. Precast elements such as walls, slabs and stairs were also used for greater efficiency.&nbsp;</span></div><div><span style=\"font-size: 18px; font-family: Helvetica;\">&nbsp;</span></div><div><span style=\"font-size: 18px; font-family: Helvetica;\">In August 2022, Megawide won in the Mid-Rise Category at Philippine Excellence in Concrete Construction Awards (PECCA) for work on the Plumera Mactan project. The award recognizes projects exhibiting outstanding use of concrete construction technology.</span></div><div><br></div><div><br></div>', NULL, '2023-06-29 11:04:36', '2023-06-29 11:04:36', NULL),
(198, 'Feeling behind on IT language? We’ve got you covered!', '<div style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px; font-family: Helvetica;\"><br></span></div><div style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px; font-family: Helvetica;\">Imagine a wide-eyed first-jobber, opening an email that reads like a foreign language.&nbsp;</span></div><div style=\"text-align: left;\"><br></div><div style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px; font-family: Helvetica;\">\"Revert with deliverables by EOD, if not ASAP, per Superior X.\"&nbsp;</span></div><div style=\"text-align: left;\"><br></div><div style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px; font-family: Helvetica;\">Corporate speak sounds so important, yet it can be so hard to decode. At some point, all of us have Googled terms used in the office or, if we’re not shy about it, asked colleagues for clarification.</span></div><div style=\"text-align: left;\"><br></div><div style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px; font-family: Helvetica;\">But if you’re intent on communicating well, it’s best to do homework in advance.</span></div><div style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px; font-family: Helvetica;\">&nbsp;</span></div><div style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px; font-family: Helvetica;\">Information Technology (IT) is a vital component in the workplace, but its language isn’t the most accessible. To give you a guide, we\'ve compiled some helpful terms with definitions. These should come in handy the next time the friendly IT person requires a meet.</span></div><div style=\"text-align: left;\"><br></div>', NULL, '2023-06-29 11:04:36', '2023-07-07 03:09:30', NULL),
(199, 'A gift of blood, a gift of life: Megawide Corporate organizes blood-donation drive', '<div><span style=\"font-size: 18px; font-family: Helvetica;\">Megawide Corporate Admin conducted last May 26 a blood-donation drive for the benefit of its employees, an initiative which is part of the department’s strong commitment to Occupational Safety and Health.</span></div><div><br></div><div><span style=\"font-size: 18px; font-family: Helvetica;\">In partnership with Red Cross, 25 employees from Megawide Corporate, PH1 and Citicore helped raised a total of 25 blood bags.&nbsp;</span></div><div><br></div><div><span style=\"font-size: 18px; font-family: Helvetica;\">“This is the first time that Megawide Corporate launched a blood-donation activity and we appreciate those who made time in participating. We look forward to doing more this year,” shared Melissa Salilican, Megawide Corporate Admin Supervisor.&nbsp;</span></div><div><br></div><div><span style=\"font-size: 18px; font-family: Helvetica;\">Megawide business units have also been active in conducting such worthy cause. Megawide Construction had its &lt;pang-ilan&gt; blood-donation drive &lt;title&gt; last &lt;month&gt;, while Precast and Construction Solutions’s 13th “Dugong Galing sa Puso” is scheduled on June 16.&nbsp;</span></div><div><br></div>', NULL, '2023-06-29 11:04:36', '2023-06-29 11:04:36', NULL),
(200, 'Megawide execs, middle management equipped with media readiness', '<div><span style=\"font-size: 18px; font-family: Helvetica;\">Corporate Communications, in partnership with Learning and Development Department, organized this year’s Media Workshops for Megawide employees assigned to face the press.&nbsp;</span></div><div><br></div><div><span style=\"font-size: 18px; font-family: Helvetica;\">The workshops covered two parts, the Executive Spokesperson Media Presence in May 13 and Middle Management Crisis Communications in May 16 and 18, providing comprehensive trainings on brand personification and media readiness.&nbsp;</span></div><div><br></div><div><span style=\"font-size: 18px; font-family: Helvetica;\">Archie Inlong, international management team coach and a veteran in crisis communications and media, facilitated the workshops sharing insights, useful techniques and frameworks in developing, enhancing and protecting public image and brand reputation.&nbsp;</span></div><div><br></div><div><span style=\"font-size: 18px; font-family: Helvetica;\">“The executive media session was an eye opener for me. I did not know there are simple ways of answering difficult questions without sounding offensive,” shared Rolando Bondoy, AVP for Investor Relations.</span></div><div><br></div><div><span style=\"font-size: 18px; font-family: Helvetica;\">“The training equipped us with meaningful and practical insights on arresting issues before they can escalate and communicating clearly to our stakeholders so mutual understanding and respect can be achieved,” shared Jaworski Alipon, Public Affairs and Communications Lead of Cebu2World.&nbsp;</span></div><div><br></div><div><span style=\"font-size: 18px; font-family: Helvetica;\">The media workshops were capped off with mock interviews by media personalities Tina Dumlao, Business Editor of Philippine Daily Inquirer and Gerard Dela Pena, News Anchor for TV5, where participants used their learnings from the workshops.&nbsp;</span></div><div><br></div><div><span style=\"font-size: 18px; font-family: Helvetica;\">Click these links to watch the media workshops!</span><br><br></div><div><span style=\"font-size: 18px; font-family: Helvetica;\">&lt;link to execs spokesperson&gt;</span></div><div><span style=\"font-size: 18px; font-family: Helvetica;\">&lt;link to crisis comms&gt;</span></div><div><br></div>', NULL, '2023-06-29 11:04:36', '2023-07-07 03:03:04', NULL);
